# Pallet Packer — environment variables
#
# VITE_API_URL
#   The ORIGIN of the packing API the app talks to (the client owns the /api/v1 path).
#
#   - BUILD-TIME ONLY: this value is read via import.meta.env and baked into the static
#     bundle at `npm run build` / `docker build`. Changing the backend requires a REBUILD.
#   - REQUIRED for production builds. A production build with no VITE_API_URL throws at
#     module load (fail-loud), so you cannot ship a misconfigured URL-less image silently.
#   - NOT needed for `npm run dev`: the Vite dev server proxies /api to the API for you,
#     so local development needs neither this var nor CORS configuration.
#
#   SAME-ORIGIN OPTION: set VITE_API_URL=/ to make the browser issue relative, same-origin
#   /api/... requests. Use this with docker-compose.local-api.yml, where the frontend's nginx
#   reverse-proxies /api/ to a co-located API container — no public API domain and no CORS.
#
# Copy this file to a build-arg / CI variable; do NOT rely on a committed .env for builds.

VITE_API_URL=https://packerapi.anzozulia.xyz
# Same-origin reverse-proxy deployment instead (see docker-compose.local-api.yml):
# VITE_API_URL=/
